1
00:00:21,321 --> 00:00:24,057
Queen:
<i>I don't believe this!</i>

2
00:00:24,057 --> 00:00:26,326
There's only four of them!

3
00:00:31,297 --> 00:00:34,234
They beat 1,200 players
all on their own?

4
00:00:37,170 --> 00:00:38,438
( grunts )

5
00:00:44,811 --> 00:00:47,781
Enough, this ends now!

6
00:01:08,068 --> 00:01:09,936
( chuckles )

7
00:01:09,936 --> 00:01:11,638
Queen:
<i>You're mine.</i>

8
00:01:25,085 --> 00:01:26,587
( gasps )

9
00:01:28,555 --> 00:01:32,325
Queen:
<i>No! You can't</i>
<i>dodge that.</i>

10
00:01:32,325 --> 00:01:34,227
<i>You can't dodge that!</i>

11
00:01:37,363 --> 00:01:40,166
Boy:
<i>Tell me if this story</i>
<i>rings a bell.</i>

12
00:01:40,166 --> 00:01:42,102
<i>It may just be an urban legend,</i>

13
00:01:42,102 --> 00:01:42,936
<i>but I assure you,</i>

14
00:01:42,936 --> 00:01:44,204
<i>it's a good one.</i>

15
00:01:44,204 --> 00:01:45,238
<i>There exists a band</i>

16
00:01:45,238 --> 00:01:46,406
<i>of anonymous players,</i>

17
00:01:46,406 --> 00:01:49,309
<i>gamers who obliterate</i>
<i>anyone who comes to face them,</i>

18
00:01:49,309 --> 00:01:51,945
<i>reaching scores never</i>
<i>achieved before or since.</i>

19
00:01:51,945 --> 00:01:55,782
<i>In every game they play,</i>
<i>their win records are flawless.</i>

20
00:01:55,782 --> 00:01:58,251
<i>Since their user names</i>
<i>are always left empty,</i>

21
00:01:58,251 --> 00:02:01,454
<i>they are simply known</i>
<i>to people as "Blank."</i>

22
00:02:01,454 --> 00:02:04,024
<i>And according to every player</i>
<i>who has encountered them,</i>

23
00:02:04,024 --> 00:02:06,226
<i>they're indeed unbeatable.</i>

24
00:02:06,226 --> 00:02:07,460
Cheaters?

25
00:02:07,460 --> 00:02:09,162
You think that's how
they keep winning?

26
00:02:09,162 --> 00:02:10,430
Yeah. I'm sure of it.

27
00:02:10,430 --> 00:02:12,666
It's got to be just
a lousy group of hackers.

28
00:02:12,666 --> 00:02:15,802
Come on, there's no way
they could beat 1,200 people

29
00:02:15,802 --> 00:02:16,603
with just the four of them.

30
00:02:16,603 --> 00:02:20,106
Auto‐aimers and wall hacks,
hitbox manipulation.

31
00:02:20,106 --> 00:02:21,107
They got to be cheating.

32
00:02:21,107 --> 00:02:22,776
Oh, do they?

33
00:02:22,776 --> 00:02:25,345
And here I thought cheating
was our expertise.

34
00:02:25,345 --> 00:02:26,980
<i>Otherwise,</i>
<i>I'd wouldn't be able</i>

35
00:02:26,980 --> 00:02:28,682
<i>to cast so many spells</i>
<i>like that.</i>

36
00:02:28,682 --> 00:02:30,617
Man:
<i>I don't know.</i>
<i>This is different.</i>

37
00:02:30,617 --> 00:02:32,385
Queen:
<i>But Blank dodged them anyway.</i>

38
00:02:32,385 --> 00:02:33,854
<i>They already knew</i>
<i>I was cheating</i>

39
00:02:33,854 --> 00:02:37,791
<i>to cast consecutive spells</i>
<i>before I even did it.</i>

40
00:02:37,791 --> 00:02:39,159
They're amazing.

41
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:41,528
They're like super geniuses
or something!

42
00:02:41,528 --> 00:02:43,263
You think maybe
they'd go out with me?!

43
00:02:43,263 --> 00:02:47,033
Man:
Oh, God.
Queen:
( cackling )

44
00:02:47,033 --> 00:02:49,770
Boy:
<i>And so the rumors spread with</i>
<i>their infamy.</i>

45
00:02:49,770 --> 00:02:53,874
<i>You know, urban legends</i>
<i>are like a kind of wish.</i>

46
00:02:53,874 --> 00:02:55,075
<i>Because...</i>

47
00:02:55,075 --> 00:02:56,342
( powers down )

48
00:02:56,342 --> 00:02:59,145
<i>in reality...</i>

49
00:02:59,145 --> 00:03:01,582
<i>the least interesting answer</i>

50
00:03:01,582 --> 00:03:04,284
<i>is usually the correct one.</i>

51
00:03:05,485 --> 00:03:10,290
( sighs )
We won... somehow.

52
00:03:10,724 --> 00:03:11,725
( sighs )

53
00:03:11,725 --> 00:03:14,427
Hey, listen, Little Sis,
could you do me a favor

54
00:03:14,427 --> 00:03:16,997
<i>and please stop controlling</i>
<i>the main account for Blank</i>

55
00:03:16,997 --> 00:03:18,198
<i>with your feet?</i>

56
00:03:18,198 --> 00:03:19,299
<i>Kind of nasty.</i>

57
00:03:19,299 --> 00:03:22,335
Hungry, I'm still hungry.

58
00:03:23,303 --> 00:03:26,072
Want some, Sora?

59
00:03:26,072 --> 00:03:27,841
Sora:
Sure, why not?

60
00:03:29,175 --> 00:03:32,779
<i>( electronic music plays )</i>

61
00:03:34,781 --> 00:03:38,619
Sora:
<i>Really splurging on some</i>
<i>fancy rations, huh, Shiro?</i>

62
00:03:38,619 --> 00:03:41,187
Shiro:
<i>Nutrition's important.</i>

63
00:03:41,187 --> 00:03:43,056
Listen, the human brain
can function

64
00:03:43,056 --> 00:03:44,424
as long as it has glucose.

65
00:03:44,424 --> 00:03:47,060
White bread is best
in terms of cost‐performance.

66
00:03:47,060 --> 00:03:48,895
Yeah.
Thanks for the lecture.

67
00:03:48,895 --> 00:03:51,131
But I need other types
of nutrients, too,

68
00:03:51,131 --> 00:03:52,766
or I won't get any bigger.

69
00:03:52,766 --> 00:03:55,335
Sora:
<i>You're already a perfect,</i>
<i>flawless beauty,</i>

70
00:03:55,335 --> 00:03:56,637
<i>you darling girl.</i>

71
00:03:56,637 --> 00:03:59,573
Mm.
Sora:
Hey, what time is it?

72
00:03:59,573 --> 00:04:02,876
Shiro:
<i>Um... 8:00 A. M.,</i>
<i>the middle of the night.</i>

73
00:04:02,876 --> 00:04:06,046
Sora: What day?
Does that even
matter to a NEET?

74
00:04:06,046 --> 00:04:06,647
It does!

75
00:04:06,647 --> 00:04:09,215
It tells me when MMORPGs
are going to have new events!

76
00:04:09,215 --> 00:04:10,684
And wha‐ wait!

77
00:04:10,684 --> 00:04:12,452
I know you've been up
for five days straight,

78
00:04:12,452 --> 00:04:15,789
but if you quit now,
I won't have a healer!

79
00:04:15,789 --> 00:04:16,857
I know you can do it.

80
00:04:16,857 --> 00:04:19,392
You seriously think
I can control four characters

81
00:04:19,392 --> 00:04:22,696
at one time?
Shiro:
Just believe.

82
00:04:22,696 --> 00:04:24,497
Wait, no!
Please don't fall asleep!

83
00:04:24,497 --> 00:04:25,932
<i>If you go to sleep,</i>
<i>Shiro, everyone‐</i>

84
00:04:25,932 --> 00:04:28,068
<i>and by everyone,</i>
<i>I mean me‐ will die!</i>

85
00:04:28,068 --> 00:04:31,171
<i>( shouts )</i>
<i>Okay, fine, fine,</i>
<i>I'll do it!</i>

86
00:04:31,171 --> 00:04:34,074
<i>I can take these suckers!</i>
<i>( mouse clicking rapidly )</i>

87
00:04:34,074 --> 00:04:37,844
<i>(birds chirping)</i>

88
00:04:37,844 --> 00:04:42,248
Boy:
<i>This world is chaotic,</i>
<i>unfair, and unforgiving.</i>

89
00:04:42,248 --> 00:04:43,850
<i>It has no meaning or value.</i>

90
00:04:43,850 --> 00:04:47,521
<i>However, some people simply</i>
<i>refuse to accept this,</i>

91
00:04:47,521 --> 00:04:50,356
<i>even though they know</i>
<i>they can't change anything.</i>

92
00:04:50,356 --> 00:04:52,025
<i>They wish that</i>
<i>the world could be</i>

93
00:04:52,025 --> 00:04:54,494
<i>just a little more interesting.</i>

94
00:04:54,494 --> 00:04:56,963
<i>And that's how</i>
<i>urban legends are formed,</i>

95
00:04:56,963 --> 00:04:59,499
<i>from wishes like that.</i>

96
00:04:59,499 --> 00:05:01,768
<i>Okay, so let's get</i>
<i>things started.</i>

97
00:05:01,768 --> 00:05:04,538
<i>Let's offer a subtle</i>
<i>stylistic catalyst</i>

98
00:05:04,538 --> 00:05:06,439
<i>for a chance</i>
<i>at a new beginning.</i>

99
00:05:06,439 --> 00:05:08,942
<i>Let's ask the question...</i>

100
00:05:08,942 --> 00:05:11,745
<i>"Have you ever heard</i>
<i>the latest rumor?"</i>

101
00:05:11,745 --> 00:05:13,313
<i>(tablet beeps)</i>

102
00:05:13,313 --> 00:05:14,247
Email.
Sora:
Listen, your brother's been
playing four characters

103
00:05:14,247 --> 00:05:17,017
Sora:
Listen, your brother's been
playing four characters

104
00:05:17,017 --> 00:05:18,184
on four separate screens.

105
00:05:18,184 --> 00:05:20,186
I don't know what you want,
but I'm seriously about

106
00:05:20,186 --> 00:05:24,257
to drop dead here.
Shiro:
It may be from a friend.

107
00:05:24,257 --> 00:05:27,193
Whose friend?
Shiro:
Your friend?

108
00:05:27,193 --> 00:05:28,895
( wheezes and laughs)
That's weird.

109
00:05:28,895 --> 00:05:31,231
I thought I heard my sister
say something really mean

110
00:05:31,231 --> 00:05:33,366
and sarcastic to me.

111
00:05:36,202 --> 00:05:37,804
Huh?

112
00:05:39,272 --> 00:05:40,941
Sora:
<i>What is this?</i>

113
00:05:40,941 --> 00:05:44,911
<i>And how does this guy know that</i>
<i>the two of us are siblings?</i>

114
00:05:46,246 --> 00:05:47,748
What should we do?

115
00:05:50,116 --> 00:05:53,554
Sora:
<i>Is he trying to</i>
<i>cut a deal with us?</i>

116
00:05:53,554 --> 00:05:57,924
Well, it might be fun
to see where this goes.

117
00:06:01,294 --> 00:06:02,696
Huh? Chess?

118
00:06:02,696 --> 00:06:05,666
Shiro:
<i>Well, good night.</i>
<i>( thud )</i>

119
00:06:05,666 --> 00:06:07,233
Huh, wait, wait!
Don't fall asleep yet.

120
00:06:07,233 --> 00:06:10,604
I can't handle a high‐level
chess simulation on my own!

121
00:06:12,539 --> 00:06:15,241
Sora:
<i>Chess is a finite</i>
<i>two‐player, zero‐sum,</i>

122
00:06:15,241 --> 00:06:17,277
<i>perfect information game.</i>

123
00:06:17,277 --> 00:06:18,845
<i>Luck plays no part in it.</i>

124
00:06:18,845 --> 00:06:21,447
<i>Theoretically, to each game,</i>
<i>there is a perfect solution</i>

125
00:06:21,447 --> 00:06:23,517
<i>that will never fail.</i>

126
00:06:23,517 --> 00:06:26,452
<i>Of course, that's only</i>
<i>if you have a mind capable</i>

127
00:06:26,452 --> 00:06:31,124
<i>of calculating</i>
<i>the 10'^120 possible states</i>

128
00:06:31,124 --> 00:06:32,826
<i>of the board.</i>

129
00:06:34,528 --> 00:06:36,530
Shiro:
Chess is no different

130
00:06:36,530 --> 00:06:39,866
than simply playing
tic‐tac‐toe.

131
00:06:42,302 --> 00:06:43,870
That's right.

132
00:06:43,870 --> 00:06:45,772
Sora:
<i>Shiro has beaten</i>
<i>a program designed</i>

133
00:06:45,772 --> 00:06:49,009
<i>to defeat grandmasters</i>
<i>20 times in a row,</i>

134
00:06:49,009 --> 00:06:52,478
<i>alternating between</i>
<i>going first and second.</i>

135
00:06:52,478 --> 00:06:54,447
<i>However...</i>

136
00:06:55,281 --> 00:06:56,850
( gasps )

137
00:06:56,850 --> 00:06:59,686
Shiro:
<i>It cut off</i>
<i>its own piece's advance.</i>

138
00:06:59,686 --> 00:07:02,088
Hold on, Shiro.
What?

139
00:07:02,088 --> 00:07:04,725
A program will always
select the best strategy.

140
00:07:04,725 --> 00:07:06,593
You can win 'cause
they're predictable.

141
00:07:06,593 --> 00:07:10,030
But this one's deliberately
using a bad move

142
00:07:10,030 --> 00:07:10,964
<i>to lure you in.</i>

143
00:07:10,964 --> 00:07:12,966
Sora:
It's a human.
Shiro:
Hmm...

144
00:07:12,966 --> 00:07:14,568
Don't worry, if it's
a contest of skill,

145
00:07:14,568 --> 00:07:16,002
you've got this
in the bag.

146
00:07:16,002 --> 00:07:19,305
<i>Sora:</i>
<i>I'll tell you when they're up</i>
<i>to something tricky.</i>

147
00:07:19,305 --> 00:07:21,307
<i>The two of us,</i>
<i>Sora and Shiro,</i>

148
00:07:21,307 --> 00:07:22,843
<i>form two halves of a whole.</i>

149
00:07:22,843 --> 00:07:25,411
<i>Now let's see</i>
<i>if there's somebody</i>

150
00:07:25,411 --> 00:07:27,814
who's got the balls
to beat us.

151
00:07:32,418 --> 00:07:35,288
( both groan )

152
00:07:35,288 --> 00:07:39,325
Male computerized voice:
<i>Checkmate! You are winner!</i>

153
00:07:39,325 --> 00:07:41,161
( both sigh )

154
00:07:41,161 --> 00:07:43,764
( yawning )
Yeah, we won!

155
00:07:43,764 --> 00:07:47,100
I haven't worked
this hard in a long time.

156
00:07:47,100 --> 00:07:48,935
Was that guy really human?

157
00:07:48,935 --> 00:07:50,070
<i>( chimes )</i>

158
00:07:50,070 --> 00:07:52,238
Together:
Huh?

159
00:07:58,378 --> 00:08:00,547
What the hell?

160
00:08:06,019 --> 00:08:09,355
Sora:
<i>What do you mean,</i>
<i>"is it fun?"</i>

161
00:08:09,355 --> 00:08:11,558
<i>In this game there's no way</i>
<i>to know the rules</i>

162
00:08:11,558 --> 00:08:14,595
<i>or how to win,</i>
<i>yet there are 7 billion players</i>

163
00:08:14,595 --> 00:08:16,429
<i>all making whatever</i>
<i>moves they want.</i>

164
00:08:16,429 --> 00:08:18,398
<i>If you lose too much,</i>
<i>or win too much,</i>

165
00:08:18,398 --> 00:08:20,200
<i>there are penalties.</i>

166
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:21,101
<i>You can't pass your turn,</i>

167
00:08:21,101 --> 00:08:23,469
<i>and if you complain,</i>
<i>people look down on you.</i>

168
00:08:23,469 --> 00:08:24,805
<i>There's no parameters</i>

169
00:08:24,805 --> 00:08:27,508
<i>or freakin' genre</i>
<i>or anything.</i>

170
00:08:27,508 --> 00:08:29,242
<i>You know what you call that?</i>

171
00:08:29,242 --> 00:08:30,343
<i>You call it...</i>

172
00:08:30,343 --> 00:08:32,579
Sora and Shiro:
<i>A crappy game.</i>

173
00:08:33,914 --> 00:08:35,215
<i>( chimes )</i>

174
00:08:40,286 --> 00:08:42,255
( laughs )

175
00:08:42,255 --> 00:08:45,491
Sora:
Uh, believe me,
if there's a world like that,

176
00:08:45,491 --> 00:08:46,893
then the two of us,

177
00:08:46,893 --> 00:08:50,664
<i>well, we were born</i>
<i>in the wrong one, for sure.</i>

178
00:08:51,364 --> 00:08:52,766
( both gasp )

179
00:08:53,499 --> 00:08:55,301
(static buzzing)

180
00:08:55,301 --> 00:08:58,972
Huh? What the‐
Sora?

181
00:08:58,972 --> 00:09:01,642
Boy:
<i>You know what?</i>
<i>I think so, too!</i>

182
00:09:01,642 --> 00:09:03,343
<i>In fact,</i>
<i>it sounds like you two</i>

183
00:09:03,343 --> 00:09:05,912
<i>don't have any business living</i>
<i>in this world at all!</i>

184
00:09:05,912 --> 00:09:08,048
( both shout )
Boy:
<i>So how does this sound?</i>

185
00:09:08,048 --> 00:09:10,817
<i>How would you like</i>
<i>a second chance to be made anew</i>

186
00:09:10,817 --> 00:09:13,186
<i>in the world in which</i>
<i>you should have been born</i>

187
00:09:13,186 --> 00:09:14,821
<i>in the first place?</i>

188
00:09:17,057 --> 00:09:20,293
<i>Welcome to the world</i>
<i>of my creation!</i>

189
00:09:20,293 --> 00:09:21,461
( both shout )

190
00:09:21,461 --> 00:09:23,229
What's going on?!

191
00:09:23,229 --> 00:09:25,431
( shouts )

192
00:09:25,431 --> 00:09:28,602
This is the ideal world
you've always dreamed of‐

193
00:09:28,602 --> 00:09:30,370
the world of games!

194
00:09:30,370 --> 00:09:30,904
It's Disboard!

195
00:09:30,904 --> 00:09:32,205
It's Disboard!
Sora:
Shit!

196
00:09:32,205 --> 00:09:34,407
You see, everything
in this world
(whimper)

197
00:09:34,407 --> 00:09:36,042
is decided by a simple game‐

198
00:09:36,042 --> 00:09:39,680
Government, politics,
even the lives of its people.

199
00:09:39,680 --> 00:09:40,714
Shiro:
Who are you?

200
00:09:40,714 --> 00:09:42,983
Me?
They call me Tet.

201
00:09:42,983 --> 00:09:45,719
I live over here.
I'm a god.

202
00:09:45,719 --> 00:09:47,453
A god?
You're so short.

203
00:09:47,453 --> 00:09:49,990
Now's not the time!
We're gonna die!

204
00:09:49,990 --> 00:09:51,357
Try to stay focused, please.

205
00:09:51,357 --> 00:09:53,894
So everything here is decided
by ten simple pledges.

206
00:09:53,894 --> 00:09:56,630
( beep )
One‐ Killing others,
waging war,

207
00:09:56,630 --> 00:09:58,398
and stealing from people
is strictly forbidden

208
00:09:58,398 --> 00:09:59,933
in this world.

209
00:09:59,933 --> 00:10:03,069
(beep)
Tet:
Two‐ All conflicts,
no matter how great or small,

210
00:10:03,069 --> 00:10:05,105
must be resolved
through games.

211
00:10:05,105 --> 00:10:06,740
<i>(beep)</i>
<i>Three‐</i>
<i>Before the games begin,</i>

212
00:10:06,740 --> 00:10:08,809
<i>each player</i>
<i>must bet something</i>

213
00:10:08,809 --> 00:10:10,243
<i>that they agree</i>
<i>is of equal value.</i>

214
00:10:10,243 --> 00:10:13,213
<i>( beep )</i>
<i>Four‐ As long as it doesn't</i>
<i>go against number three,</i>

215
00:10:13,213 --> 00:10:15,281
<i>what they bet</i>
<i>and the rules of the game</i>

216
00:10:15,281 --> 00:10:16,082
<i>will not be questioned.</i>

217
00:10:16,082 --> 00:10:19,352
<i>( beep )</i>
<i>Five‐ The challenged party has</i>
<i>the right to determine</i>

218
00:10:19,352 --> 00:10:20,987
<i>the rules of the game.</i>

219
00:10:20,987 --> 00:10:24,457
<i>( beep )</i>
<i>Six‐ All bets made in</i>
