00:20:34,901 --> 00:20:39,272
<i>This really is an</i>
<i>honest‐to‐God fantasy world.</i>

453
00:20:39,272 --> 00:20:40,807
And the way
she was cheating...

454
00:20:40,807 --> 00:20:43,276
that was like
its own fantasy, too.

455
00:20:43,276 --> 00:20:48,014
Sora, can you beat
real magic?

456
00:20:53,386 --> 00:20:56,422
I guess that
was a dumb question.

457
00:20:57,323 --> 00:20:58,859
Hey, Shiro...

458
00:20:58,859 --> 00:21:01,394
usually, in, like,
comics and stuff

459
00:21:01,394 --> 00:21:02,996
when the main characters
end up in another world,

460
00:21:02,996 --> 00:21:05,932
they try their best
to find a way home, right?

461
00:21:11,037 --> 00:21:13,306
<i>Sora:</i>
<i>But why would they want</i>
<i>to go back to a world</i>

462
00:21:13,306 --> 00:21:17,277
if it's total... shit?

463
00:21:22,348 --> 00:21:25,151
( sighs softly )

464
00:21:25,151 --> 00:21:26,753
( chuckles )

465
00:21:28,522 --> 00:21:31,692
Shiro:
I thought the same thing.

466
00:21:35,261 --> 00:21:37,631
Well, then it's settled.

467
00:21:42,569 --> 00:21:45,438
Sora:
<i>Let the real game begin.</i>

468
00:21:45,438 --> 00:21:47,841
<i>( theme song plays )</i>

469
00:23:16,597 --> 00:23:18,999
<i>( taps on door )</i>

470
00:23:27,073 --> 00:23:29,309
Shiro, as your brother,
I'm really happy

471
00:23:29,309 --> 00:23:33,446
that you love me so much,
but let go of me for a second.

472
00:23:34,347 --> 00:23:35,215
<i>( footsteps )</i>

473
00:23:35,215 --> 00:23:36,382
Sora:
<i>Who's there?</i>

474
00:23:36,382 --> 00:23:38,952
Come on, man,
I paid up front already.

475
00:23:44,758 --> 00:23:49,395
Would it be okay
if I came in for a second?

476
00:23:49,395 --> 00:23:51,632
Shiro:
We're gonna save the day?

477
00:23:51,632 --> 00:23:54,735
Sora:
<i>Sure, why not,</i>
<i>it'll be fun, right?</i>

